J.C. Lee, the daughter of the late legendary Stan Lee who is the brains behind Marvel Comics has revealed that she and her father were working on a new superhero prior to his death. J.C who yesterday, November 13 was on TMZ Live to discuss her father’s legacy disclosed that she will be pushing forward with the project of creating the brand new superhero that her father was helping her with. She revealed that the new hero is named Dirt Man and is currently in the works. She also made it known that she created the character but also credited her late father who died two days for helping her to develop the hero right up until his last weekend. When she was asked about what Dirt Man’s powers are, or his origin story, she only said, “It’s very interesting.” It would be recalled we first reported that Stan Lee died on Monday, November 12 after he was rushed to a hospital from his Hollywood Hills home.